A letter to the Honorable William Lenthal esq; Speaker of the Honorable House of Commons, from Col: Morgan Governor of Glocester, concerning the whole proceedings of the siege before Raglan-Castle. Together with the several summons of the said Colonel to the Earl of Worcester, and the Earls obstinate answers thereunto. VVhich letter and summons were appointed by the Honorable W: Lenthal Esq, Speaker of the Honorable House of Commons to be forthwith printed and published. Morgan, Thomas, Sir, d. 1679? Worcester, Henry Somerset, Marquis of, 1577-1646.
8 p.
Printed for E. Husband, printer to the Honorable House of Commons., [London] : [1646]
Place and date of publication from Wing. Annotation on Thomason copy: "July 3d". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
